[{"id":"VH919724","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Consider the following method.</p><div class=\"standalone_code style:1\"><p class=\"code_line\">public int[] transform(int[] a)</p><p class=\"code_line\">{</p><p class=\"code_line indent:3\">a[0]++;</p><p class=\"code_line indent:3\">a[2]++;</p><p class=\"code_line indent:3\">return a;</p><p class=\"code_line\">}</p></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">The following code segment appears in a method in the same class as <span class=\"inline_code\">transform</span>.</p><div class=\"standalone_code style:1\"><p class=\"code_line\">/* <span class=\"formatted_text font_style:italic font_variant:normal font_weight:normal\">missing code</span> */</p><p class=\"code_line\">arr = transform(arr);</p></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">After executing the code segment, the array <span class=\"inline_code\">arr</span> should contain <span class=\"inline_code\">{1, 0, 1, 0}</span>. Which of the following can be used to replace <span class=\"inline_code\">/*</span> <span class=\"formatted_text font_style:italic\">missing code</span> <span class=\"inline_code\">*/</span> so that the code segment works as intended?</p><ol class=\"hb_codeblock ordered_list style:1\"><li class=\"list_paragraph\"><span class=\"inline_code\">int[] arr = {0, 0, 0, 0};</span></li><li class=\"list_paragraph\"><span class=\"inline_code\">int[] arr = new int[0];</span></li><li class=\"list_paragraph\"><span class=\"inline_code\">int[] arr = new int[4];</span></li></ol>\n","rubricRef":"VH919724_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">I only</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">III only</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">I and II</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">I and III</p>"],"answer":4}]